(3) The office of member shall become vacant— (a) upon the member's death; (b) if he is adjudged bankrupt; (c) if he is adjudged or otherwise declared to be of unsound mind under any law in force in Zambia; (d) if he is absent, without prior approval of the Council from three consecutive meetings of the Council of which due notice was given to him; or (e) upon the expiry of not less than one month's notice, in writing, of that member's intention to resign given by the member to the President.
